**Project Process Flow**

**Project Title:** Legal Consultancy Platform Development

**Legal Consultancy Website \- Detailed Functional & Flow Document**

---

## **1\. Project Overview**

We are building a **legal consultancy website** where clients can select a legal service, fill in a dynamic form, upload documents, make payments via PhonePe, and get connected with a lawyer through an automatically generated Twilio video call link. The system will have a **Client Website(on [domain.com](http://domain.com) )** and an **Admin Panel ( on [domain.com/admin](http://domain.com/admin) and not a separate panel on different domain )**.

---

## **2\. Client Website Pages & Flow ( on [domain.com](http://domain.com) )**

### **2.1 Landing Page**

- Design similar to [lawfy Theme](https://themexriver.com/wp/lawfy/)

- Header with navigation to Services, About, Contact, Lawyer Registration

- Footer with standard links and contact info

- Dynamic service categories displayed (controlled by Admin)

### **2.2 Services Pages**

- Each service dynamically created/edited by Admin

- Admin can set service name, description, price, and other details

- Each service linked to a single dynamic form (created by Admin)

### **2.3 Service Flow for Client**

1. Client selects a service

2. Client fills out the linked dynamic form

3. Client uploads required documents

4. Documents uploaded to AWS S3

5. Client makes payment via PhonePe

6. Upon success, request is sent to Admin

### **2.4 Contact Page**

- Standard contact form for inquiries

### **2.5 Lawyer Registration Page**

- Form for lawyers to register

- Submitted details go to Admin Panel for approval

- Only approved lawyers are marked active and visible in Admin listings

---

## **3\. Admin Panel Pages & Functionalities**

### **3.1 Service Management**

- Add / Edit / Delete services

- Attach a single dynamic form to each service

- Set price and service details

### **3.2 Dynamic Form Builder**

- Admin can create/edit forms

- Set conditional logic for fields

- Attach form to a single service

### **3.3 Client Inquiry Management**

- View all client inquiries with:

  - Client ID, phone number, service selected

  - Payment status

  - Uploaded documents

  - Form responses

### **3.4 Lawyer Management**

- View all lawyer registration requests

- Approve/Reject requests

- Maintain list of active lawyers

- Track lawyer availability and assignments

### **3.5 Meeting Scheduling**

- Admin assigns a lawyer to a client case

- Schedule a meeting

- System generates Twilio video link

- WhatsApp notification sent to both lawyer and client

### **3.6 Status Update**

- Admin can update status of each case

- Status visible in admin panel

---

## **4\. Payment Integration**

- PhonePe payment gateway

- Success triggers case progression

- Failure prompts retry

---

## **5\. Notification System**

- WhatsApp notifications using Twilio API

- Sent to both lawyer and client for:

  - Meeting confirmation

  - Payment confirmation

  - Case updates

---

## **6\. Back-End (High Level)**

- Node.js / Express API

- PostgreSQL

- AWS S3 for document uploads

- Twilio API for video meetings & WhatsApp

- PhonePe API for payments

---

## **7\. High-Level Database Entities**

- **Users** (Clients)

- **Lawyers**

- **Services**

- **Forms**

- **Inquiries**

- **Meetings**

- **Payments**

- **Documents**

---

## **8\. End-to-End Flow**

1. **Client Website:** User selects service → fills form → uploads docs → pays → confirmation sent

2. **Admin Panel:** Admin reviews inquiry → assigns lawyer → schedules meeting → Twilio link \+ WhatsApp notifications sent

3. **Meeting Execution:** Client & lawyer join meeting → meeting auto-ends

4. **Status Update:** Admin updates status → record saved
